        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/>Sexto Petronio Probo,
                        <lb n="2"/>Anicianae domus
                        <lb n="3"/>culmini, proconsuli
                        <lb n="4"/>Africae, praefecto
                        <lb n="5"/>praetorio quater
                        <lb n="6"/>Italiae, Illyrici, Afri<lb 
                            break="no" n="7"/>cae, Galliarum, con<lb 
                            break="no" n="8"/>suli ordinario, con<lb 
                            break="no" n="9"/>sulum patri, Anicius
                        <lb n="10"/>Hermogenianus
                        <lb n="11"/>Olybrius <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ir</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>larissimus</ex></expan> consul
                        <lb n="12"/>ordinarius, et Ani<lb 
                            break="no" n="13"/>cia Iuliana <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>larissima</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>emina</ex></expan>, eius
                        <lb n="14"/>devotissimi filii,
                        <lb n="15"/>dedicarunt.
                    </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <p>Edition based on CIL.</p>
                <p></p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>“To Sextus Petronius Probus, summit of the Anicia family, proconsul of Africa, praetorian prefect for four times, of Italy, Illyricum, Africa, Gauls, ordinary consul, father of consuls, Anicius Hermogenianus Olybrius, of clarissimus rank, ordinary consul, and Anicia Iuliana, of clarissima rank, his most devote children, have dedicated.”</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="fr">
                <p>“...”</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it">
                <p>“A Sextus Petronius Probus, culmine della casata Anicia, proconsole d’Africa, prefetto del pretorio quattro volte, d’Italia, d’Illirico, d’Africa, delle Gallie, console ordinario, padre di consoli, Anicius Hermogenianus Olybrius, chiarissimo, console ordinario, e Anicia Iuliana, chiarissima, suoi figli devotissimi, dedicarono.”</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>...</p>
            </div>
